value:
Hearse cloth of gold with an applied red velvet cross with alternating applied embroidered rose and portcullis motifs, and a centrally placed coat-of-arms of Henry VII. 
Made in England with late 15th century Italian silk, and English embroidery, 1505.

summary_title: Dress at the Court of King Henry VIII, The Wardrobe Book of the Wardrobe of the Robes prepared by James Worsley in December 1516, edited from Harley MS 2284, and his Inventory prepared on 17 January 1521, edited from Harley MS 4217, both in the British Library
notes: Publ. p. 60, discussed under 'Preparations for death: Henry VII, and illustrated Fig. 4.5; see a details, p. 250, Fig. 13.5, a Tudor rose, p. 255, Fig. 14.2 a coat-of-arms
